Missiles

Missile launches on right mouse click
Precondition: Game is running, and no missiles are currently on the screen.
Action: User right-clicks the mouse.
Postcondition: A missile appears from the bottom center of the screen and travels vertically upwards.

Missile launches on space bar press
Precondition: Game is running, and no missiles are currently on the screen.
Action: User presses the space bar.
Postcondition: A missile appears from the bottom center of the screen and travels vertically upwards, similar to the right-click launch.

Exceed missile limit by attempting to launch more than five missiles
Precondition: Game is running with no missiles on the screen.
Action: User presses the space bar or right-clicks six times in rapid succession.
Postcondition: Only five missiles appear; additional launch attempts after the fifth do not result in more missiles.

Missile travels off-screen
Precondition: Game is running, and a missile is traveling upward.
Action: Allow the missile to move off the top of the screen.
Postcondition: The missile is removed from the list of active missiles on the screen.

Test missile speed and direction consistency
Precondition: Game is running with no active missiles on the screen.
Action: User presses the space bar or right-clicks multiple times in succession to launch several missiles back-to-back.
Postcondition: All missiles travel upward in a consistent manner, maintaining the same speed and direction.

Ships

Trigger new ship launch after all ships are destroyed
Precondition: Game is running, and there are no active ships on the screen.
Action: Allow all existing ships to be destroyed.
Postcondition: New ships start appearing at a 30% launch rate.

Ship count limit at maximum of 10 ships
Precondition: Game is running, with multiple ships allowed to launch.
Action: Allow multiple ships to launch until the screen fills.
Postcondition: No more than 10 ships appear on the screen simultaneously.

Ship launches from either side of the screen
Precondition: Game is running, with ships spawning actively.
Action: Observe multiple ships as they launch.
Postcondition: Ships spawn from both the left and right sides of the screen in alternating or random patterns.
Destruction

Missile hits a ship
Precondition: Game is running with at least one ship and one missile active on the screen.
Action: Launch a missile so it collides with a ship.
Postcondition: Both the missile and the ship disappear, and an animation (such as an explosion) is triggered.

Hit count increments correctly
Precondition: Game is running with a visible hit counter on the screen.
Action: Hit ships with multiple missiles, tracking the hit count.
Postcondition: The hit count increases by one for each successful missile hit on a ship.

End

Game ends after 10 hits
Precondition: Game is running with a visible hit counter, initially set below 10.
Action: Achieve 10 successful missile hits on ships.
Postcondition: The game initiates its ending sequence once 10 hits are reached.

Game ends on user-triggered action or inactivity
Precondition: Game is running.
Action: User hits the left mouse button, presses the ESC key, or allows a period of inactivity.
Postcondition: The game ends.
	 
